uk.ac.manchester.cs.mekon.owl.build

Class OBConceptHiding

  • java.lang.Object
    • uk.ac.manchester.cs.mekon.owl.build.OBConceptHiding

  • public class OBConceptHiding
extends java.lang.Object
    Specifies, for a particular section of concept-hierarchy, the set of concepts within that section for which the generated frames will be defined as "hidden".

    • Method Summary

      All Methods Instance Methods Concrete Methods

      void setCandidates(OBEntitySelection candidates)

    • Method Detail

      • setCandidates

        public void setCandidates(OBEntitySelection candidates)
        Allows the specification of which concepts from within the relevant section of hierarchy can possibly be hidden, subject to passing the filtering conditions. If not set will default to OBEntitySelection.NONE.
        Parameters:
        candidates - Specification of potentially hidden concepts

      • setFilter

        public void setFilter(OBConceptHidingFilter filter)
        Sets the filter that will be applied to the candidate concepts. If not set will default to OBConceptHidingFilter.ANY.
        Parameters:
        filter - Filter to apply to candidates concepts
